  "intro": "Every quarter, we rank the 30 highest-performing creator-made TikToks about Pittsburgh small businesses by total plays. This list generated 198,450 plays across 29 unique creators and 18 businesses, and not one of those videos came from the businesses themselves. @bhphotographypa drove 62,800 plays to a soft-serve window in Arlington. @deluludayss sent 21,400 people down an aesthetic rabbit hole that ended at a coffee shop in East Liberty. The businesses were open, the food was good, and someone else did the work of telling Pittsburgh about it.\n\nThat gap is the story we keep returning to. Creators are building audiences around this city's neighborhood spots, documenting menus, moods, and lines out the door, while the businesses themselves stay largely quiet online. It is not a critique so much as an observation with real stakes: the coverage exists, it travels, and its source has nothing to do with the people being covered.\n\nIn Issue 02, we start asking why.",
